Kenya on Tuesday recorded 318 new Covid-19 cases, bringing the total number to 41, 937. This is from 2,592Â  samples tested in the last 24 hours, bringing the cumulative number to 595,791. Of the cases, 215 are males while 103 are females. Agewise, the youngest is a three-year-old while the oldest is 90 years old. In terms of recoveries, 243 more patients have recovered from the virus, bringing the total recoveries in the country to 31,340. A total of 132 recovered from the home-based care programme, while 111 recovered from different health facilities. On a sad note, 10 people have succumbed to the virus, with the number of deaths rising to 787. More follows...